<br>
MoBs are almost all leashed. The only place where a MoB isn't leashed is in Instanced Content, and since that's instanced there's noon else in there to train you. What happens is this, a mob has a general spawn point, it can't get further than X distance from it's spawn point cause of the leash. When you have to run from somethin whoopin yer arse, and the mob chases you, it'll only chase until it hits that X distance, at which point it will immediately path back to the spawn loc about 1.5x it's normal speed. While it's running back it's in what's referred to as &quot;Evade&quot; mode... meaning it can't be hit... it'll constantly Evade any attack made on it, also it will not stop to attack another target... I've had people train 6 mobs past me while I sit down to rest and then watched em path back right beside me and not attack. When the MoB breaks combat and starts to flee it also regens HP about 10-15x it's normal rate. Basicly it WoW wants mobs to get back to their spawn point, and reset for someone to kill.<br>
<br>
There is a downside to this (if you can view it as a downside) in that you can't kite mobs... well you can but it's alot more difficult than in EQ. <br>
